{{Wireless embedded system |brand=AsiaRF |model=AWM |revision=003 |est_release_date=2014 |fcc_date=11/11/2017 |is_manuf=No |type=mini module |fcc_id=TKZAWM003 |cpu1_brand=Ralink |cpu1_model=RT5350;RT5350F, TPFBH34609, 1729STA1; |cpu1_cspeed=360 |fla1=16 |fla1_brand=Winbond |fla1_model=W25Q128FVSG |ram1=64 |ram1_brand=EtronTech |ram1_model=EM63A165TS-6G |ram1_num=2 |expansion_if_types=USB 2.0 (pins) |expansion_usb_num=1 |serial=yes |wi1_chip1_brand=Ralink |wi1_chip1_model=RT5350;RT5350F; |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_ant_conn=U.FL |wi1_txchains=1 |wi1_rxchains=1 |wi1_sstreams=1 |eth_cpu=true |lan_speed=100M |802dot11_protocols=bgn }} {{TagLine|802.11n Wireless AP Router Module Board}} :{{ProductPage|http://www.asiarf.com/product-view-386.html}}
"ASIARF", "AWM003 MAIN", "AWM003-001 REV.2", and "02-26-2014" are silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
Flash / RAM may vary, defaults are specified as 8MB / 64MB. The device pictured in FCC documents has 16MB Flash and 64MB RAM. :See also [[AsiaRF AP7260 MPE-1]]..
===Features=== *Ralink RT5350 chipset, Support boot from Flash :Multi-modes: AP/Client, Data Rate up to 150Mbps :Security: 64/128-bits WEP, TKIP,WPA, WPA2,AES,WPS :Interface: USB, I2C, I2S, PCM, UART, LED, RJ45 LAN ports and GPIO :Low Temperature max to 60 Celsius degree with full speed running
